What is Shell Scripting? WHY should you learn it?
Think of it like this:
Imagine you work in a factory. Every morning you have to:

Turn on 10 machines
Check if they're working
Write a report

Doing this manually every day = waste of time.
So you hire a robot to do it automatically.
Shell script = that robot 🤖
In DevOps, you need to:

Start/stop servers
Check if a website is up
Take backups
Deploy code

Shell scripts automate all of this.

What is a "Shell"?
When you open a terminal (black screen with text), you're talking to the Shell.
Shell = The translator between you and the computer.
You type commands → Shell understands → Computer does the work.
The most popular shell is called BASH (Bourne Again SHell). This is what we'll learn.
